Fourteen pupils have been rushed to clinics after having fallen ill at the Masonwabe Primary School in Delft, Cape Town. DELFT - Fourteen pupils have been rushed to clinics after having fallen ill at the Masonwabe Primary School in Delft, Cape Town. They apparently fainted and parents claim some children experienced seizures. Panicked parents rushed to the school where emergency staff were attending to some pupils. READ: Umlazi pupils airlifted after inhaling gas There were no answers for them as the principal had already gone home. Locals in the area are claiming it’s not the first time an incident of this nature has taken place at the school. READ: More than 200 pupils rushed to hospitals in Limpopo They claim witchcraft may be at play. The Western Cape Education Department says it’s sent support staff to the school and is investigating the incident.